Nice. This might be called "meta-linking." One problem that linkers solve
for C++ is that
the same function may be defined more than once (because more than one
source file
may include the header containing the definition). What happens is that
weak defs are
written to the object files, and the linker removes the multiple defs and
does not
complain about multiple definitions. This does not seem to be necessary with
meta-linking.


